.TH YORO 1 "June 2026" "yoro 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
yoro \- a terminal UI for local calendars and contacts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B yoro
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B yoro
is a terminal user interface for browsing calendars and contacts stored on disk
in the vdirsyncer/khal layout. It reads iCalendar (\fI.ics\fR) and vCard
(\fI.vcf\fR) files directly and presents them in a fast, vim-navigated,
miller-column interface inspired by
.BR yazi (1).
.PP
The interface has two modes \(em Calendar and Contacts \(em that share the same
navigation. The Calendar mode shows a day-grouped agenda with a mini-month
navigator and per-collection color toggles; recurring events are expanded on the
fly. The Contacts mode shows a three-column address book / contact list / detail
view with live search.
.PP
This release is read-only. Editing files and CalDAV/CardDAV synchronization are
planned.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-calendars \fIDIR\fR
Override the calendars directory (default \fI~/.local/share/calendars\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-contacts \fIDIR\fR
Override the contacts directory (default \fI~/.local/share/contacts\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Global
.TP
.B tab, 1, 2
Switch between Calendar and Contacts.
.TP
.B R
Reload all data from disk.
.TP
.B ?
Toggle the help overlay.
.TP
.B q, ctrl+c
Quit.
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B h, l
Move focus to the column on the left or right.
.TP
.B j, k
Move down or up.
.TP
.B gg, G
Jump to the top or bottom.
.TP
.B ctrl+d, ctrl+u
Half-page down or up.
.TP
.B /
Search within the current pane;
.B n
and
.B N
move to the next and previous match;
.B esc
clears.
.SS Calendar
.TP
.B t
Jump to today.
.TP
.B }, {
Jump to the next or previous day that has events.
.TP
.B J, K
Move the mini-month to the next or previous month.
.TP
.B space
Toggle the highlighted collection on or off.
.TP
.B T
Toggle visibility of tasks (VTODO).
.SS Contacts
.TP
.B y
Yank the highlighted email or phone number to the clipboard (via OSC52).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/calendars
Default calendars directory. Each subdirectory containing \fI.ics\fR files is a
calendar collection; optional \fIdisplayname\fR and \fIcolor\fR sibling files set
the name and color.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/contacts
Default contacts directory. Each subdirectory containing \fI.vcf\fR files is an
address book.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Used to locate the default data directories when set.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yazi (1),
.BR khal (1),
.BR vdirsyncer (1)
